DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-4076(83)90059-3
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304407683900593
AB  - In this paper we propose a non-nested hypothesis test for testing the specification of a multivariate econometric model in the presence of an alternative model which purports to explain the same phenomenon. We demonstrate that the new test statistic tends to minus the same random variable as the CPD test statistic introduced by Pesaran and Deaton (1978), provided that the truth is ‘close’ to the null hypothesis. Since the new test is simpler to compute than the multivariate CPD test, it would seem to be the procedure of choice.
